description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 6 Community Mental Health Nurses&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It’s a great time to be a part of the Community Mental Health Teams in West Kent as we have been awarded additional Mental Health Funding to expand the teams which will enable us to develop the Clinical Care Pathways leading to an improved and innovative service for our Service Users, Carers and Staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We can offer flexibility regarding hours and are able to offer long days, part-time and job share opportunities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;West Kent Maidstone Community Mental Health Team are based in both Maidstone and Tunbridge Wells and are a diverse multi-cultural team that is looking to recruit a Band 6 Mental Health Nurses to work within the team, providing specialist mental health care for people with multiple and complex needs that require intensive support. You can be based at either Tunbridge Wells or Maidstone depending on your location however the posts will provide services to both locations so travel between both sites will be required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If are interested in either a Duty Role, Assessments, Care Co-ordination or a mixture of all of these roles we would like to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our service focuses on promoting recovery for those people diagnosed with severe and enduring mental ill health. We provide comprehensive multi-disciplinary services and work closely with local specialist mental health teams, tertiary service providers, primary care, local statutory and non-statutory agencies, service users and carers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Care Group is currently implementing new Clinical Care Pathways these are Initial Interventions, Personality Disorder and Enduring Condition so there will be opportunity for you to choose a specialism should you be the right person.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;What we can offer you in West Kent:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;- Participation in groups with Psychology and Occupational Therapy &lt;br /&gt;- Opportunities to run groups&lt;br /&gt;- Preceptorship for new qualified staff&lt;br /&gt;- Leadership Modules to develop in senior roles&lt;br /&gt;- Mentorship and Supervision&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Relocation package (if meets criteria)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;What you can expect once you join the team: &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;- Monthly supervision (clinical and managerial)&lt;br /&gt;- Reflective Group to discuss complex cases and share learning &lt;br /&gt;- MDT Risk Forum to discuss complex cases with high risks &lt;br /&gt;- Mandatory training &lt;br /&gt;- Clinical Review of caseload with Consultant Psychiatrist and Team Leader&lt;br /&gt;- Structured Clinical Management Group support&lt;br /&gt;- Admin support &lt;br /&gt;- Peer support &lt;br /&gt;- Free parking&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We are looking for motivated and enthusiastic Mental Health Practitioners. You will have a strong sense of initiative and an excellent team working ability. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Effective communication skills and self-governance are required. You will be able to demonstrate knowledge of high level interventions &amp; community assessment skills. Existing qualifications or a willingness to undertake training relevant to the post is expected.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This post offers an excellent opportunity to work in an interesting and developing service environment and if you have no experience of working in the community but would like to expand your professional development then we can offer you a development programme to support you with this transition. You will be offered considerable opportunities for training and professional development.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;As part of the Band 6 Nursing team you will be required to attain a mentoring qualification.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Louise Rigg or Indi Randhawan, Operational Team Managers on 01622 766900&lt;/p&gt;
